Vladimir Bukovsky has lived in the UK since he fled the Soviet Union in the 1970s . 
  He was accused of spreading anti-Soviet propaganda and spent 12 years in prison and forced labour camps . 
  He has been summonsed to appear at Cambridge Magistrates Court on May 5 . 
  The 72-year-old will be charged with making and possessing indecent images of children . 
  He denies the allegations and will appear at court next month . 
 